3465	  \textit{Project-bespoke gap-fill (instance).}
3466	  The forgetful functor from sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules to the underlying sheaves of
3467	  abelian groups preserves epimorphisms: if \(g : S_2 \to S_3\) is an epimorphism of
3468	  \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules then the induced morphism of underlying abelian sheaves is an
3469	  epimorphism. Indeed the forgetful functor is exact (it has both adjoints and reflects the relevant
3470	  colimits), so it carries the cokernel-zero characterisation of an epimorphism to the same
3471	  characterisation downstairs. This is the one small instance unlocking the passage from a module
3472	  epimorphism to local surjectivity in Lemma~\ref{lem:affine_surj_of_vanishing}.
3473	\end{lemma}
3474	\begin{proof}
3475	  An epimorphism in an abelian category is characterised by vanishing cokernel. The underlying
3476	  abelian-sheaf functor on sheaves of \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-modules is additive and exact (it preserves
3477	  finite colimits, being a left adjoint composed with the exact sheafification–forgetful comparison),
3478	  so it sends the cokernel of \(g\) to the cokernel of the image of \(g\); since the former is zero,
3479	  so is the latter, and the image of \(g\) is an epimorphism.
3480	\end{proof}
